Package seedu.address.logic.parser

Class ArgumentMultimap

  • java.lang.Object
    • seedu.address.logic.parser.ArgumentMultimap

  • public class ArgumentMultimap
extends java.lang.Object
    Stores mapping of prefixes to their respective arguments. Each key may be associated with multiple argument values. Values for a given key are stored in a list, and the insertion ordering is maintained. Keys are unique, but the list of argument values may contain duplicate argument values, i.e. the same argument value can be inserted multiple times for the same prefix.

      • put

        public void put​(Prefix prefix,
                java.lang.String argValue)
        Associates the specified argument value with prefix key in this map. If the map previously contained a mapping for the key, the new value is appended to the list of existing values.
        Parameters:
        prefix - Prefix key with which the specified argument value is to be associated
        argValue - Argument value to be associated with the specified prefix key

      • getValue

      • getAllValues

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getAllValues​(Prefix prefix)
        Returns all values of prefix. If the prefix does not exist or has no values, this will return an empty list. Modifying the returned list will not affect the underlying data structure of the ArgumentMultimap.

      • getPreamble

        public java.lang.String getPreamble​()
        Returns the preamble (text before the first valid prefix). Trims any leading/trailing spaces.
